00:59.112 --> 01:00.562
Hello?

01:00.564 --> 01:02.731
Maeve, it's me. Listen, don't come
to the restaurant.

01:02.733 --> 01:04.816
What are you talking about?
I'm outside.

01:04.819 --> 01:05.784
Go home.

01:05.786 --> 01:08.120
Look, I think
your stalker's here.

01:41.304 --> 01:43.489
Have you the ring?

01:50.980 --> 01:52.614
Place the ring
on her finger.

01:52.616 --> 01:54.483
On whose finger?

01:55.668 --> 01:57.836
Oh.

02:06.679 --> 02:08.514
I now pronounce you smart

02:08.515 --> 02:09.882
and smarter.

02:09.883 --> 02:11.717
Let's get to it, you two.

02:11.719 --> 02:12.834
Get to what?

02:12.836 --> 02:15.220
Kiss her, dummy.

03:02.653 --> 03:03.769
Hello.

03:03.771 --> 03:06.105
Hello.
I have a collect call from...

03:06.107 --> 03:09.491
Adam Worth.

03:09.493 --> 03:11.393
Operator; Do you accept
the charges?

03:11.395 --> 03:12.528
Yes.

03:12.530 --> 03:16.165
Please deposit $2.00
for the first two minutes.

03:27.410 --> 03:29.077
Thank you.

03:30.414 --> 03:33.215
Hello. I'm still here.

03:33.217 --> 03:37.603
Zug...zwang.

03:38.888 --> 03:41.640
I'm sorry, can you
please repeat that?

03:41.642 --> 03:43.108
Zug...

03:43.110 --> 03:45.060
zwang.

03:47.431 --> 03:49.764
I got here as quickly
as I could.

03:49.766 --> 03:51.400
What's wrong?

03:51.402 --> 03:53.285
I need to tell you
something.

03:56.789 --> 03:59.774
Our correspondence started
10 months ago.

03:59.776 --> 04:02.961
She wrote me a compliment on my
"Journal of Behavioral Psych" article,

04:02.963 --> 04:04.921
and for 3 months,
this is how we communicated

04:04.946 --> 04:06.249
because she was scared.

04:06.250 --> 04:07.949
Scared of whom?

04:07.951 --> 04:11.286
She didn't know,
only that he was dangerous.

04:11.288 --> 04:13.863
Horribly threatening
phone calls, letters, emails,

04:13.888 --> 04:15.291
no matter where she moved.

04:15.292 --> 04:18.125
It's why I never called her
from the same phone booth twice.

04:18.128 --> 04:19.478
You don't know
what Maeve looks like?

04:19.480 --> 04:20.478
No.

04:20.481 --> 04:21.512
Or where she works?

04:21.515 --> 04:22.981
No. I know
she's a geneticist.

04:22.983 --> 04:24.833
Do you even know
her last name?

04:27.070 --> 04:29.988
Then I have to ask you,
how do you know she's missing?

04:29.990 --> 04:32.157
Because we always addressed
our letters to pseudonyms.

04:32.159 --> 04:33.775
And you're
Dr. Joseph Bell?

04:33.777 --> 04:36.161
The real-life inspiration
for Sherlock Holmes.

04:36.163 --> 04:38.480
And that codename
is how I know she's in trouble.

04:38.482 --> 04:42.084
The voice on the phone
identified himself as Adam Worth.

04:42.086 --> 04:44.597
That was the American criminal
that Arthur Conan Doyle based

04:44.622 --> 04:46.456
the character of Moriarty on.

04:46.457 --> 04:48.090
And what did he say
to you?

04:48.092 --> 04:50.325
Zugzwang.

04:50.327 --> 04:52.327
It's a chess term.

04:52.329 --> 04:53.879
It describes the point
in a game

04:53.881 --> 04:57.015
when a player realizes
he'll inevitably be checkmated.

04:57.017 --> 04:59.184
He has to decide
whether to resign

04:59.186 --> 05:02.104
or to play through
to the bitter end.

05:02.106 --> 05:04.056
If you're right about this,

05:04.058 --> 05:07.392
then you're part of
his victimology, too.

05:07.394 --> 05:11.012
I know.

05:11.014 --> 05:12.731
He thinks he'll get away
with this,

05:12.733 --> 05:15.484
and he might.

05:15.486 --> 05:18.853
I have a wealth of knowledge
I should be applying to this case.

05:18.855 --> 05:21.356
Behavioral patterns
of violent stalkers.

05:21.358 --> 05:23.041
Tactical recovery
strategies.

05:23.043 --> 05:24.576
Victim survival odds.

05:24.578 --> 05:27.246
But right now I can't
focus on anything

05:27.248 --> 05:29.081
more than 4 seconds
at a time.

05:29.083 --> 05:31.250
Which makes me the dumbest
person in the room.

05:31.252 --> 05:33.385
So...

05:33.387 --> 05:36.471
Please help me.

05:36.473 --> 05:38.307
Help me find her.

05:39.592 --> 05:41.977
We don't know
if we have a case.

05:43.212 --> 05:45.147
So we'll be working
on personal time.

05:46.249 --> 05:48.600
Does anybody want to leave?

05:51.554 --> 05:52.738
Good.

05:52.740 --> 05:53.971
Let's get to work.

